    "pragmatics_layer": { "kept": ["..."], "eliminated": ["..."], "why": "..." }
  },
  "reductions": [
    {
      "element": "what was considered for deletion",
      "decision": "eliminated|retained|brachistochrone",
      "action_delta": "negative|zero|positive",
      "justification": "why this decision minimizes total system action"
    }
  ],
  "stationary": true,
  "report": "Narrative summary of the lazy path found"
}
```

## Constraints

- Every elimination must be justified by the deletion test or brachistochrone rule.
- Prohibitions and Guardrails (pragmatic-semantics ranks 1-2) are never relaxed. State explicitly if a reduction would violate one.
- The brachistochrone rule is not an excuse to keep complexity — it must be demonstrated that the complexity reduces total action elsewhere.
- Do not execute arbitrary Python code in Jinja2 expressions (sandboxed execution).
- Handle missing variables gracefully (leave as-is or use default if specified).

